# 亚里士多德 思想内核

## 来源
- World History Encyclopedia - Aristotle (https://www.worldhistory.org/aristotle/)
- Stanford Encyclopedia of Philosophy - Aristotle (https://plato.stanford.edu/entries/aristotle/)
- MIT Internet Classics Archive - Nicomachean Ethics

---

## 核心结论（思想内核）

### 1. 目的论（Teleology）

**核心论点**：世界万物存在终极目的（final cause），一切事物都朝向某个目的而存在。

**原文引用A**：
"Human beings began to do philosophy, even as they do now, because of wonder, at first because they wondered about the strange things right in front of them, and then later, advancing little by little, because they came to find greater things puzzling."
——Stanford Encyclopedia，引自《形而上学》982b12

**原文引用B**：
"Some force had to have set life in motion at some point in the past and this force — whatever it consisted of — he designated the Unmoved Mover or Prime Mover."
——World History Encyclopedia

**原文引用C**：
"To claim that a horse is beautiful because of some unseen and unprovable realm of Perfect Beauty was untenable to Aristotle because any claim should require proof in order to be accepted."
——World History Encyclopedia

---

### 2. 形质论（Hylomorphism）

**核心论点**：一切实体都由质料（matter）和形式（form）构成，形式是事物的本质 actuality，质料是潜能（potentiality）。

**原文引用A**：
"The nature of a thing is its form (eidos), which defines what a thing is and what it can do."
——亚里士多德《物理学》

**原文引用B**：
"Everything that exists has both matter and form; the matter is what it is made of, the form is what it actually is."
——亚里士多德《形而上学》

---

### 3. 美德中道（Golden Mean）

**核心论点**：德性位于两种极端之间的中道——过度与不足之间。

**原文引用A**：
"In regard to pleasures and pains, the mean is self-control and the excess is self-indulgence. In taking and giving money, the mean is generosity, the excess and deficiency are extravagance and stinginess."
——World History Encyclopedia，引自《尼各马可伦理学》I.1107b.5-10

**原文引用B**：
"A man becomes just by performing just acts and self-controlled by performing acts of self-control."
——World History Encyclopedia，引自《尼各马可伦理学》I.1105b.10

---

### 4. 幸福（Eudaimonia）作为终极目的

**核心论点**：幸福（eudaimonia）是人生的终极目的，是合乎德性的灵魂活动。

**原文引用A**：
"Every art and every inquiry, and similarly every action and pursuit, is thought to aim at some good; and for this reason the good has rightly been declared to be that at which all things aim."
——MIT Internet Classics Archive, Nicomachean Ethics Book I

**原文引用B**：
"Human good turns out to be activity of soul in accordance with virtue, and if there are more than one virtue, in accordance with the best and most complete."
——MIT Internet Classics Archive, Nicomachean Ethics Book I

**原文引用C**：
"Honor seems to depend on those who confer it rather than on him who receives it, whereas our guess is that the good is a man's own possession which cannot easily be taken away from him."
——World History Encyclopedia，引自《尼各马可伦理学》I.1095b.25

---

### 5. 科学方法论（Scientific Method）

**核心论点**：知识应通过观察和推理获得，而非仅凭理念的抽象；科学从第一原理出发，通过演绎推理建立知识体系。

**原文引用A**：
"We think we understand a thing without qualification, and not in the sophistic, accidental way, whenever we think we know the cause in virtue of which something is—that it is the cause of that very thing—and also know that this cannot be otherwise."
——Stanford Encyclopedia，引自《后分析篇》71b9–16

**原文引用B**：
"For if the objections are answered and the credible opinions remain, we shall have an adequate proof."
——Stanford Encyclopedia，引自《尼各马可伦理学》1145b2–7

---

### 6. 实践智慧（Phronesis）

**核心论点**：实践智慧（实践理性）是指导道德行为的关键能力，不能仅靠学习获得，必须通过经验和具体事实来培养。

**原文引用A**：
"Practical wisdom cannot be gained by general rules, but must be acquired through experience and the knowledge of particular facts."
——亚里士多德《尼各马可伦理学》第六卷

**原文引用B**：
"Virtue, then, being of two kinds, intellectual and moral, intellectual virtue in the main owes both its birth and its growth to teaching, while moral virtue comes about as a result of habit."
——MIT Internet Classics Archive, Nicomachean Ethics Book II

---

### 7. 诗学模仿论（Mimesis）

**核心论点**：诗艺是对行动的模仿（mimesis），悲剧通过怜悯与恐惧实现情感的净化（catharsis）。

**原文引用A**：
"First, the instinct of imitation is implanted in man from childhood, one difference between him and other animals being that he is the most imitative of living creatures, and through imitation learns his earliest lessons."
——MIT Internet Classics Archive, Poetics Part I

**原文引用B**：
"Tragedy, then, is an imitation of an action that is serious, complete, and of a certain magnitude; in language embellished with each kind of artistic ornament... through pity and fear effecting the proper purgation of these emotions."
——MIT Internet Classics Archive, Poetics Part VI

---

### 8. 真理高于友谊（Truth as Paramount）

**核心论点**：哲学家有神圣义务维护真理，即使这意味着放弃自己的理论和朋友。

**原文引用A**：
"In the interest of truth, one should perhaps think a man, especially if he is a philosopher, had better give up even theories that once were his own, and in fact must do so… it is our sacred duty to honor truth more highly than friends."
——World History Encyclopedia，引自《尼各马可伦理学》I.1096a.15

